19/07/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The OSCE and the US government are funding a new office to combat trans-national crime that opened in Belgrade Monday (18 July). 
The Secretariat of the South East European Prosecutors Advisory Group will facilitate collaboration among prosecutors from Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, Greece, Macedonia, Moldova, Romania, Serbia-Montenegro, Slovenia and Turkey. 
OSCE mission deputy chief Douglas Wake stressed that a regional approach and co-operation is crucial to success in the fight against organised crime. 
(Politika - 19/07/05; OSCE Web site, Tanjug, B92 - 18/07/05)
